title: India Today - 26 September 2016 (gnv64)
description:
India Today - 26 September 2016
English | 135 pages | True PDF | 28.7 mb

India Today is an Indian weekly news magazine published by Living Media India Limited, in publication since 1975 based in New Delhi. It currently has a circulation of over 1.1 million copies with a readership of over 5.62 million. 
The cover story this week, Bone of Affliction, is on how Vitamin D deficiency is becoming the newest lifestyle disease that is claiming our attention and the extent of the threat it poses. The story - Price of Neglect - is all about the Cauvery water dispute and how the Supreme Court's order to Tamil Nadu to release water for Karnataka led to violent protests. With Bihar strongman Mohammad Shahabuddin walking out of Siwan jail after 11 long years, the story 'Casting a Long Shadow' looks at what implications his bail have on the Bihar government and Chief Minister Nitish Kumar. The issue also carries a special report on Haryana Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar's governance and his plans to deliver his party's poll promises. The issue also comes with three free magazines: Home, Simply Gujarati, Simply Mumbai.
